methods.name: showGenericModal
methods.description:
Opens an Ionic component modal with the content and attributes passed in the function params

Example :
```typescript
const comp = ExampleAngularComponent;
const props = {text: 'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.'};
const id = 'modal-unique-id';
const modal = await showGenericModal(comp, id, props, canDismiss);
console.log(modal); // 'accept' || undefined
Example :

jsdoctags.comment: • The Angular component that shoud be shown in the modal
• An object with the Inputs used in the component
• The ID attribute assigned to the modal | default 'dialog-modal'
Will return undefined or a string with the action taken by user click

Example :
const comp = ExampleAngularComponent;
const props = {text: 'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.'};
const id = 'modal-unique-id';
const modal = await showGenericModal(comp, id, props, canDismiss);
console.log(modal); // 'accept' || undefined

propertiesClass.name: classes

components.templateData:
<button [class]="classes()" [disabled]="disabled()">
  @if (spinner() && spinnerPosition() == 'left') {
    <ion-spinner [name]="spinner()" [color]="color()"></ion-spinner>
  }
  @if (icon() && iconPosition() == 'left') {
    <ion-icon [name]="icon()"></ion-icon>
  }
  {{ label() }}
  @if (icon() && iconPosition() == 'right') {
    <ion-icon [name]="icon()"></ion-icon>
  }
  @if (spinner() && spinnerPosition() == 'right') {
    <ion-spinner [name]="spinner()" [color]="color()"></ion-spinner>
  }
</button>
